CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 26, 1959, pg. B2, reads: "In Celebration of Pittsburgh's Bicentennial - Pa. Training School Marks 'Pioneer Day' - Doing His Best - During the 'Pioneer Day' celebration at Pennsylvania Training School last Saturday, Johnny Morton, well known among his Pittsburgh friends for his feats with knife and fork, takes time out to show his prowess with a well-filled plate. Mr. Morton is principal of the boys' school. At the rear, right, is Miss Elluvise Inabinet, principal of the girls' school. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Johnny Morton wearing straw boater and striped jacket holding plate of food, with Elluvise Inabinet in background, during eating contest for "Pioneer Day" celebration at Pennsylvania Training School, Canonsburg
